It was playing in the hospital when my mom died.

241
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:31,085
I'm sorry, Peyton.

242
00:13:31,281 --> 00:13:32,711
No, it's...

243
00:13:34,321 --> 00:13:39,535
Anyway, happiest song would be "Happy Birthday."

244
00:13:39,650 --> 00:13:42,030
I'm partial to any song that ends with cake.

245
00:13:42,279 --> 00:13:43,337
What about you?

246
00:13:44,666 --> 00:13:47,680
"Here comes a regular" -- The Replacements.

247
00:13:47,773 --> 00:13:51,310
Huh. Not exactly an up-tempo number.

248
00:13:51,423 --> 00:13:54,019
Yeah, but there's a great story behind it.

249
00:13:54,139 --> 00:13:56,073
Right before graduation, I went with some friends

250
00:13:56,153 --> 00:14:00,334
to this big outdoor music festival in Winston-Salem.

251
00:14:00,439 --> 00:14:03,343
It was in the middle of a field called the Meadow.

252
00:14:03,984 --> 00:14:05,539
Night comes.

253
00:14:06,264 --> 00:14:09,637
And this terrible thunderstorm rolls in -- 

254
00:14:10,664 --> 00:14:13,137
thunder, lightning.

255
00:14:13,258 --> 00:14:14,766
None of the bands could play.

256
00:14:14,859 --> 00:14:18,161
30,000 people, mud up to our knees,

257
00:14:18,265 --> 00:14:19,778
waiting it out,

258
00:14:20,479 --> 00:14:23,197
praying for the storm to break.

259
00:14:23,937 --> 00:14:25,525
